    "updated": "2026-04-22",
    "description": "Per-state links to the official state-legislator lookup tool plus a universal fallback. Used by /petition.html and /find-my-reps.html when a visitor enters a ZIP: we can resolve their U.S. House district from data/zips.json but not yet their state-senate / state-house district. Rather than silently omit that half of their civic stack, we link out to the authoritative state tool and to OpenStates as a universal fallback. All URLs verified against their respective authoritative domains; where an official tool accepts a URL-param deep-link for ZIP or address, the pattern is documented in the state's entry.",
    "sources": {
      "state_websites": "Each state's own .gov or .state.xx.us domain.",
      "openstates": "https://openstates.org/find_your_legislator/ — non-partisan civic-tech project run by Plural (formerly the Sunlight Foundation), covers all 50 states."
    },
    "roadmap_note": "A full ZIP -> SLDU/SLDL crosswalk would let us resolve state-legislative districts directly. Building that from Census TIGER/Line shapefiles or OpenStates' API is the natural next step; this lookup-link manifest is the honest intermediate."
  },
